ike chimneys with flames just coming right up them,'' Artist said. Shifting winds, gusting up to 22 mph, made it difficult for firefighters to contain the blaze. The fire shifted directions several times because of the winds, officials said. `` One time it's going down the hills, then seconds later it's going up the hills faster than it came down,'' Artist said <PERSON> Lynne </PERSON> <PERSON> Cechettini </PERSON>, 16, was napping when her sister woke her up and told her about the fire. `` I looked out the kitchen and there was this huge flame wall and I thought for sure our house was gone,'' said <PERSON> Cechettini </PERSON>, whose hair was filled with ashes. Only the roof of the Cechettini's home burned. The homes were situated among grassland dotted by patches of <LOCATION> California </LOCATION> scrub oaks, pine and eucalyptus trees and low-lying bushes.
