<HEAD>Emmys Highest Rated Show Yet for Fox</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By KATHRYN BAKER</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>AP Television Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The Emmys show was fledgling <ORGANIZATION> Fox </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Broadcasting </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>'s highest-rated ever even though it was the second lowest-rated Emmys presentations, according to <ORGANIZATION> A.C. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Nielsen </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> figures. `` The 40th Annual Emmy Awards'' broadcast Sunday ranked 33rd among network shows with a rating of 10.4 and an 18 share, <PERSON> Fox </PERSON>'s highest showing among the networks <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION> won the night with `` Police Academy 2: First Assignment.'' <PERSON> Fox </PERSON> also trailed CBS' `` Blood and Orchids, Part 1,'' but that did n't faze Fox President <PERSON> Jamie </PERSON> <PERSON> Kellner </PERSON>. `` I'm very pleased to be the No. 3 network nationally,'' he said. `` I also think that we put a great show on. `` It's the first time we've ever over-delivered for advertisers, so it was good for them, too,'' <PERSON> Kellner </PERSON> said. He said <PERSON> Fox </PERSON> had guaranteed a 10.0 rating. Last year's Emmys was the lowest-rated ever with an 8.8 its first of three years on <PERSON> Fox </PERSON>. When <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION> carried the Emmys in 1986, it got a rating of 23.7 and a 36 share. Otherwise, it was a week of reruns with <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION>'s `` The Cosby Show'' back in first place. The rest of the top 10 included <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION>'s `` A Different World,'' `` Cheers'' and `` Night Court,'' CBS' `` 60 Minutes'' and `` Murder, She Wrote,'' <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION>'s `` Police Academy 2,'' `` Golden Girls,'' `` Amen'' and `` <PERSON> Hunter </PERSON>.'' <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION> won the week that ended Sunday with an average, prime-time rating of 12.2. <ORGANIZATION> CBS </ORGANIZATION> had a 9.7 and <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION> had 8.9. But the three-network share of 56 percent was a rebound from the all-time low 47 during the week of the Republican National Convention. Each rating point represents the antion's 886,000 households with televisions. The share is a percentage of sets in use. In the evening news race, `` ABC World News Tonight'' pulled into the lead with a 9.3 rating and 20 share. The `` CBS Evening News'' was second with a 9.0 and 20. `` NBC Nightly News'' remained in third with an 8.6 and 18 share.
