OCATION>. The East German delegation boycotted the meeting. Some Korean writers also have boycotted the meeting, saying they would not attend until their colleagues were released from jail. `` Many members think it's not nice to go to banquets when there are colleagues in prison,'' <PERSON> von </PERSON> <PERSON> Vegesack </PERSON> said. The `` Writers in Prison'' committee was even approached, he said, by representatives from <LOCATION> North </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Korea </LOCATION> `` who wanted to give us information not about the situation in their own country, but about the situation in <LOCATION> South </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Korea </LOCATION>.'' He said the committee ignored the overture.
