otected for 18 years, as a solution to Mr. <PERSON> Sallah </PERSON>'s problem,'' said <PERSON> Sabin </PERSON> <PERSON> Guertin </PERSON>, a <ORGANIZATION> Canterbury </ORGANIZATION> resident for 65 years. The Sallahs have taken the issue to <ORGANIZATION> Merrimack </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> County </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Superior </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Court </ORGANIZATION> and have stopped work on the house, which is enclosed but not finished inside. The owners of the ranch-style home also are appealing the zoning board's requirement that they put shingles on the house.
