<HEAD>4,000 Starved To Death In South, Tens of Thousands Threatened</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By MOHAMED OSMAN</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>KHARTOUM, Sudan (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Four thousand men, women and children have died of starvation and tens of thousands residing in the war-torn regions of southern <LOCATION> Sudan </LOCATION> face a similar fate, officials said Wednesday. <PERSON> Angelo </PERSON> <PERSON> Beda </PERSON>, president of <LOCATION> Sudan </LOCATION>'s Council for the South, said the only way to save those starving in the <LOCATION> Equatoria </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Bahr </LOCATION> <LOCATION> el-Ghazal </LOCATION> regions was with emergency air shipments of food and medical supplies. In <LOCATION> Ireland </LOCATION>, the Rev. <PERSON> Aengus </PERSON> <PERSON> Finucane </PERSON>, director of the Dublin-based aid agency CONCERN said about 40 people were dying daily at a refugee camp in el <LOCATION> Meriam </LOCATION>, 500 miles south of <LOCATION> Khartoum </LOCATION>, and that about 2 million people faced death from the ravages of war and starvation. <PERSON> Beda </PERSON> said most southerners abandoned their crops and cattle in the countryside and fled to towns and cities because of fierce fighting in the five-year civil war. He said residents are being beseiged by the rebel <ORGANIZATION> Sudan </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> People </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> 's </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Liberation </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Army </ORGANIZATION> and dying of starvation as food supplies dwindle. <PERSON> Beda </PERSON>, whose group includes southern political representatives from Prime Minister <PERSON> Sadek </PERSON> <PERSON> el-Mahdi </PERSON>'s government, said record floods in <LOCATION> Sudan </LOCATION> earlier this month diverted the attention of Western relief organizations from what he called the `` catastrophe'' of the south. `` Four thousand people have died of hunger in -LRB- the town of -RRB- <LOCATION> Aweil </LOCATION> so far,'' he said. <LOCATION> Aweil </LOCATION>, in the <LOCATION> Bahr </LOCATION> <LOCATION> el-Ghazal </LOCATION> region, is 587 miles southwest of <LOCATION> Khart