 rebel attacks, relief agencies have been sporadically flown in supplies from neighbouring countries, or used trucks, trains and barges from <LOCATION> Khartoum </LOCATION>. The rebels, mostly Christians and animists, are seeking more autonomy as well as economic and administrative reforms from the Moslem majority government in the north.
