where film and televison crews move to non-union states and countries. `` The issue is competitiveness,'' said <PERSON> Herb </PERSON> <PERSON> Steinberg </PERSON>, a spokesman for the alliance. `` We want to remain competitive in this market and keep production here.'' The producers estimate that runaway production has cost <ORGANIZATION> Hollywood </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Teamsters </ORGANIZATION> $ 14 million in lost wages and benefits during the last two years. The producers also want to redefine rules for overtime pay.
