<HEAD>Airline Industry Analysts Say Delta's Reputation Should Survive
Intact</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Delta Crash Bjt</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Subs 13th graf, `Anthony Hatcher...' to CORRECT name to
Hatch.</NOTE>
<BYLINE>By JOHN A. BOLT</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>AP Business Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>ATLANTA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Delta </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Lines </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> has grown from a cropduster to the nation's third-largest airline since it began operations six decades ago flying from <LOCATION> Dallas </LOCATION> to <PERSON> Jackson </PERSON>, Miss. A <ORGANIZATION> Delta </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Boeing </ORGANIZATION> 727, Flight 1141 which originated in <LOCATION> Jackson </LOCATION>, crashed on takeoff Wednesday at <LOCATION> Dallas-Fort </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Worth </LOCATION> <LOCATION> International </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Airport </LOCATION>. The crash came three years and 26 days after a <ORGANIZATION> Delta </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Lockheed </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> L-1011 </ORGANIZATION> jet crashed at the same airport, killing 137 people. Lawsuits seeking millions of dollars in damages from that crash are still in court, although some already have resulted in multimillion-dollar judgments against <ORGANIZATION> Delta </ORGANIZATION>. Last year, <ORGANIZATION> Delta </ORGANIZATION> suffered a spate of embarrassments: Pilots landed at the wrong airport or on the wrong runway; one plane plummeted toward the ocean because the pilot mistakenly shut off the engines; another plane was involved in a near miss over the <LOCATION> Atlantic </LOCATION>. Last year, <ORGANIZATION> Delta </ORGANIZATION> also grew by acquiring <ORGANIZATION> Western </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Airlines </ORGANIZATION> in an $ 860 million merger. Through it all, <ORGANIZATION> Delta </ORGANIZATION> has maintained a reputation as a well-run, safe and financially secure airline. `` I do n't think the reputation is undeserved,'' and it probably wo n't change, said <PERSON> Robert </PERSON> <PERSON> Decker </PERSON>, an airline industry analyst with <ORGANIZATION> Duff </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> ; </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZ