<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Resorts </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> International </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> stockholders have approved entertainer <PERSON> Merv </PERSON> <PERSON> Griffin </PERSON>'s offer to buy the gaming and real estate company. But <PERSON> Griffin </PERSON>'s proposed trust agreement _ needed before he can buy Resorts stock from those shareholders and controlling stockholder <PERSON> Donald </PERSON> <PERSON> Trump </PERSON> _ failed to win approval from the state <ORGANIZATION> Casino </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Control </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Commission </ORGANIZATION> on Tuesday. The trust agreement is necessary in case the commission finds <PERSON> Griffin </PERSON> ineligible for a <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Jersey </LOCATION> gaming license.
