<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
 The stock market finished mixed Tuesday in a slow session. The Dow Jones average of 30 industrial stocks fell 3.20 to 2,038.23, but broader market measurements were mostly higher. The dollar slipped against all major currencies except the Japanese yen. Bond prices finished slightly higher after trading in a narrow range. Pork futures prices plunged for the second straight day, while grain and soybean futures rose sharply, precious metals drifted lower, energy futures advanced and stock-index futures retreated.
