o assist ailing S & amp; Ls, including a major deal in <LOCATION> Texas </LOCATION>, which like <LOCATION> Oklahoma </LOCATION> has been hard hit by the depression in the oil drilling industry. On another front, the bank board was facing a self-imposed deadline to wrap up negotiations with the <ORGANIZATION> Robert </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> M. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bass </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Group </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Fort </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Worth </ORGANIZATION>, <LOCATION> Texas </LOCATION>, which is seeking federal assistance to acquire <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Savings </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> and </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Loan </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Association </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stockton </ORGANIZATION>, <LOCATION> Calif. </LOCATION>, one of the nation's largest S & amp; Ls. The board began negotiating with the <ORGANIZATION> Bass </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Group </ORGANIZATION> exclusively on April 21 and twice has extended the deadline, with the most recent extension expiring Thursday. <PERSON> Hoyle </PERSON> said the board would have an announcement regarding American by Thursday. Industry sources have said between $ 1.3 billion and $ 2 billion in federal money will be required for the rescue.
